commit.message:
Enable IPv6 support of stunnel by default

There is following comment before the variable definition of
mew-ssl-localhost.

;; stunnel does not support IPv6, sigh

However, it seems recent version of stunnel works fine with IPv6.
So enable IPv6 support by default. Also remove above comment as it
doesn't make sence any more.

Add GnuTLS support for SMTP, IMAP, POP, and NNTP

Mew now supports GnuTLS library for TLS connections when the Emacs
is built with it.  To enable it, set mew-ssl-default to 'native.

mew-{imap,nntp,pop,smtp}-ssl now accept the following symbols:

native - Use GnuTLS (this requires Emacs compiled with GnuTLS
         library).  When mew-smtp-ssl-port is equal to
         mew-smtp-port, a plain connection will be opened and
         upgraded by STARTTLS.
tunnel - Use an external program to establish a TLS tunnel.
         stunnel(1) utility is used by default.

The value of mew-ssl-default is used when mew-{imap,nntp,pop,smtp}-ssl
is 't'.

Merge PR #160

add support of mew-config-alist for SSL proxy.

when using SSL proxy in mew-config-alist, define ssl-proxy-server and
ssl-proxy-port as follows,

---
(setq mew-config-alist
      '(
	("sample"
	 ("ssl-proxy-server" . "192.168.192.100")
	 ("ssl-proxy-port" . "8080")
	 )))

add support ssl connection via proxy.

setq two variables for proxy, like the followings,

(setq mew-ssl-proxy-server "proxy-server.example.com")
(setq mew-ssl-proxy-port "8080")
